bug.summary: [Codelab]: Making Predictions from 2D Data - Spelling mistake
bug.description:
Spelling mistake on the tutorial TensorFlow.js — Making Predictions from 2D Data <denchmark-link:https://codelabs.developers.google.com/codelabs/tfjs-training-regression/index.html#6>https://codelabs.developers.google.com/codelabs/tfjs-training-regression/index.html#6</denchmark-link>
We generate 100 new ‘examples' to feed to the model. Model.predict is how we feed those examples into the model. Note that they need to be have a similar shape ([num_examples, num_features_per_example]) as when we did training.

comments.comment: <denchmark-link:https://github.com/benjaminfiliatrault>@benjaminfiliatrault</denchmark-link> thanks for reporting. This is noted and corrected , will be available whenever next push happens.
